  <source>University of California, Berkeley</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      People who buy insurance are sicker and/or more risk averse than those who don't. Also,
      Micro-health insurance increases utilization of public health care facilities and protects
      against asset sales.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Randomly assign coupons giving a discounted price for insurance. Since coupon receipt is
      exogenous, use these coupons as an instrument for take-up of insurance.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
